WEBVTT

1
00:00:53.138 --> 00:00:54.764
Why did you wanna hide this?

2
00:00:57.475 --> 00:00:59.102
- Who is it?
- Porter.

3
00:01:00.478 --> 00:01:01.479
Two secs.

4
00:01:11.656 --> 00:01:12.657
Thanks.

5
00:01:24.586 --> 00:01:28.131
I'm guessing he had his skull crushed in
with the butt of his own shotgun.

6
00:01:29.549 --> 00:01:30.884
It couldn't have been easy.

7
00:01:31.801 --> 00:01:34.929
Marnes was made of iron. anger and spite.

8
00:01:34.930 --> 00:01:36.139
Who are you?

9
00:01:36.723 --> 00:01:38.515
- This is Paul Billings. He's your...
- Oh.

10
00:01:38.516 --> 00:01:40.142
That's the guy you wanted to be sheriff.

11
00:01:40.143 --> 00:01:41.937
He's your new Chief Deputy.

12
00:01:42.520 --> 00:01:43.939
The old one's not even cold.

13
00:01:51.738 --> 00:01:54.241
Well. Marnes was right.
Someone really wanted him dead.

14
00:01:55.617 --> 00:01:56.867
Do we have control of this?

15
00:01:56.868 --> 00:01:59.870
- His door was open. A neighbor found him.
- Can we keep a lid on it?

16
00:01:59.871 --> 00:02:00.788
We could try.

17
00:02:00.789 --> 00:02:02.123
If we don't. we're fucked.

18
00:02:07.170 --> 00:02:10.047
This could've all been avoided
if our new sheriff had posted someone

19
00:02:10.048 --> 00:02:13.217
- to watch Marnes tonight.
- Your new sheriff offered. and he said no.

20
00:02:13.218 --> 00:02:15.511
- So I heard. You should've ignored him.
- Oh. you heard. huh?

21
00:02:15.512 --> 00:02:17.930
Yeah. I stopped by
and saw him and his bloody nose.

22
00:02:17.931 --> 00:02:20.850
- Who gave him a bloody nose?
- One of his many fans.

23
00:02:22.561 --> 00:02:23.770
It's the mortuary team.

24
00:02:26.106 --> 00:02:28.817
All right. let's go to my office.

25
00:02:29.317 --> 00:02:30.360
My new office.

26
00:02:37.450 --> 00:02:39.035
Can you tell them to give me a minute?

27
00:02:41.788 --> 00:02:42.872
One minute.

28
00:04:00.575 --> 00:04:02.160
Hey. uh. you can go in.

29
00:04:10.085 --> 00:04:12.545
I'm only gonna be mayor for a few months.

30
00:04:12.546 --> 00:04:18.050
so I'm gonna try to drink as much
of Mayor Jahns's liquor as I can.

31
00:04:25.642 --> 00:04:26.643
Hmm.

32
00:04:32.023 --> 00:04:33.149
So...

33
00:04:35.610 --> 00:04:37.987
What do we do?

34
00:04:37.988 --> 00:04:40.030
Just keeping pumping the official line.

35
00:04:40.031 --> 00:04:42.449
Two older people walked the Silo.
it was too much for them.

36
00:04:42.450 --> 00:04:44.368
- See your doctor...
- No. we bury them together.

37
00:04:44.369 --> 00:04:45.536
Sorry. what?

38
00:04:45.537 --> 00:04:48.831
One funeral. One grave.
Conservation of resources.

39
00:04:48.832 --> 00:04:51.918
Times like this. people don't
give a shit about conservation.

40
00:04:54.296 --> 00:04:55.297
But...

41
00:04:57.132 --> 00:04:59.550
- we could say they were in love.
- Were they?

42
00:04:59.551 --> 00:05:01.927
The way they nagged
at each other. I always wondered.

43
00:05:01.928 --> 00:05:03.512
Mmm. Doesn't matter. though.

44
00:05:03.513 --> 00:05:06.932
I don't know if there's anything
in the Pact about a double funeral.

45
00:05:06.933 --> 00:05:09.184
- Paul?
- For a married couple. but. um...

46
00:05:09.185 --> 00:05:11.604
- The mayor can make an exception.
- Why would the mayor do that?

47
00:05:11.605 --> 00:05:13.398
So it becomes the story. Rob.

48
00:05:14.524 --> 00:05:18.986
A couple of old servants of the Silo.
enjoying a late bloom of love.

49
00:05:18.987 --> 00:05:21.363
looking to spend
their golden years together.

50
00:05:21.364 --> 00:05:23.949
only to have their lives
cut tragically short.

51
00:05:23.950 --> 00:05:26.785
If they were in a relationship.
it was unsanctioned.

52
00:05:26.786 --> 00:05:28.455
At their age. who gives a fuck?

53
00:05:29.039 --> 00:05:33.543
And if people do care. it's even better.
Gets people talking about forbidden love.

54
00:05:34.836 --> 00:05:36.212
Anything but murder.

55
00:05:36.213 --> 00:05:37.881
We need a distraction.

56
00:05:38.381 --> 00:05:39.590
It's a good idea. Sheriff.

57
00:05:39.591 --> 00:05:43.511
For a distraction. the judge suggested
we offer a Forgiveness Holiday.

58
00:05:44.012 --> 00:05:46.765
- It's good for morale.
- It's good for Judicial.

59
00:05:49.017 --> 00:05:51.728
Now. let's push
the story that they were in love.

60
00:05:52.312 --> 00:05:55.065
Then I am going to announce
a Race to the Top.

61
00:05:55.565 --> 00:05:58.651
Say Mayor Jahns loved a good footrace.

62
00:05:58.652 --> 00:06:00.862
Award the Jahns trophy to the victor.

63
00:06:02.030 --> 00:06:06.034
People love an excuse
to drink beer and yell.

64
00:06:06.534 --> 00:06:07.785
Jahns hated those races.

65
00:06:07.786 --> 00:06:09.870
She always thought
they would get out of hand.

66
00:06:09.871 --> 00:06:10.956
Hmm.

67
00:06:15.252 --> 00:06:17.754
I'll let you two go. Get some sleep.

68
00:06:18.547 --> 00:06:20.048
Sheriff. would you stay a minute?

69
00:06:26.096 --> 00:06:29.099
You know. you're the reason
I stopped by to see Marnes last night.

70
00:06:29.975 --> 00:06:32.269
I said we should make Paul sheriff now.

71
00:06:32.894 --> 00:06:34.187
Marnes said to wait.

72
00:06:35.313 --> 00:06:37.231
Not because he thought you'd succeed.

73
00:06:37.232 --> 00:06:39.441
He figured you'd realize
you were in over your head

74
00:06:39.442 --> 00:06:41.569
and slink back down
to Greasetown on your own.

75
00:06:41.570 --> 00:06:44.739
All right. All right. that's enough.
Give it a rest. Rob.

76
00:07:00.463 --> 00:07:01.464
You don't like it.

77
00:07:02.632 --> 00:07:07.387
I'm installing Billings as Chief Deputy
without your say-so.

78
00:07:09.472 --> 00:07:10.599
Have you read the Pact?

79
00:07:11.683 --> 00:07:12.683
Yeah. some of it.

80
00:07:12.684 --> 00:07:14.602
Start with the section on your department.

81
00:07:14.603 --> 00:07:19.315
It doesn't explicitly say
that a sheriff should kiss Judicial's ass.

82
00:07:19.316 --> 00:07:22.903
but it's pretty much
the subtext on every page.

83
00:07:59.981 --> 00:08:00.982
Um...

84
00:08:01.775 --> 00:08:05.277
This morning. I ran a program

85
00:08:05.278 --> 00:08:11.534
to create a data set
of Silo residents under the age of 46.

86
00:08:12.535 --> 00:08:19.000
A number I arrived at
by taking 40 and adding 6.

87
00:08:19.501 --> 00:08:24.088
Forty being the amount of years
that Ruth Jahns served as mayor.

88
00:08:24.089 --> 00:08:28.676
and six being the age
of basic societal awareness.

89
00:08:28.677 --> 00:08:30.387
giving a total...

90
00:08:31.638 --> 00:08:37.101
of 5.496 Silo residents

91
00:08:37.769 --> 00:08:42.106
out of the current population of 10.112.

92
00:08:42.816 --> 00:08:47.903
for whom Ruth Jahns
was the only mayor they ever knew.

93
00:08:47.904 --> 00:08:49.405
Mm-hmm.

94
00:08:49.406 --> 00:08:53.201
Mayor Jahns was a trusted
and beloved leader

95
00:08:53.702 --> 00:08:58.540
because she knew
the residents of the Silo.

96
00:08:59.165 --> 00:09:00.375
and they knew her.

97
00:09:02.168 --> 00:09:05.170
Thankfully. I am but an interim mayor

98
00:09:05.171 --> 00:09:08.550
until someone can be elected

99
00:09:09.050 --> 00:09:12.679
to fill Ruth Jahns's very large shoes.

100
00:09:13.471 --> 00:09:18.893
Um. and not her literal shoes
because she...

101
00:09:18.894 --> 00:09:22.063
Actually. her feet were rather small.

102
00:09:25.483 --> 00:09:26.735
Hmm.

103
00:09:27.444 --> 00:09:28.445
Uh. Sheriff.

104
00:09:29.112 --> 00:09:32.198
Would you like to say a few words
about Deputy Marnes?

105
00:09:37.037 --> 00:09:38.079
Um...

106
00:09:39.789 --> 00:09:41.791
I honestly don't know
what to say about Marnes.

107
00:09:44.211 --> 00:09:46.962
He and I didn't exactly. um. hit it off.

108
00:09:46.963 --> 00:09:50.717
He. uh. he didn't want me as. um. sheriff.

109
00:09:51.426 --> 00:09:55.138
I think he shared that
with a lot of people. I guess.

110
00:09:56.223 --> 00:09:59.141
I didn't want the job at first.

111
00:09:59.142 --> 00:10:02.311
But then I was told that if
the mayor asks you to serve.

112
00:10:02.312 --> 00:10:04.356
you-you serve.

113
00:10:06.024 --> 00:10:10.194
And here I am.
speaking at Marnes's burial.

114
00:10:10.195 --> 00:10:12.781
in front of people
who knew him better than I did.

115
00:10:13.823 --> 00:10:14.824
Sad people.

116
00:10:17.911 --> 00:10:19.495
I'm not... I'm not sad.

117
00:10:19.496 --> 00:10:22.624
I. um... I mean. it's...
It's sad that he died. of course.

118
00:10:23.208 --> 00:10:26.253
But his...
His life. their lives. they. um...

119
00:10:27.671 --> 00:10:28.922
They're worth celebrating.

120
00:10:30.465 --> 00:10:35.636
They dedicated their lives to the Silo.
like we all do every day.

121
00:10:35.637 --> 00:10:40.725
Like everyone does.
from the Up Top to the Down Deep.

122
00:10:52.153 --> 00:10:53.572
Hear us. oh. Founders.

123
00:10:55.198 --> 00:11:00.287
Ruth Jahns and Samuel Marnes
served your Silo with their spirit.

124
00:11:01.997 --> 00:11:05.792
and now will serve with their flesh.

125
00:11:06.877 --> 00:11:09.546
Death into life.

126
00:11:11.339 --> 00:11:13.717
Circle without end.

127
00:12:07.812 --> 00:12:08.980
Hank?

128
00:12:10.565 --> 00:12:12.358
Jules.

129
00:12:12.359 --> 00:12:14.401
- Hey.
- What are you doing here?

130
00:12:14.402 --> 00:12:18.782
Oh. I. uh... I got an invite to the burial.

131
00:12:19.783 --> 00:12:21.158
Really? I didn't see you there.

132
00:12:21.159 --> 00:12:24.119
Yeah. Um. funerals aren't really my thing.

133
00:12:24.120 --> 00:12:27.248
Yeah. they're not really anyone's thing.

134
00:12:27.249 --> 00:12:29.251
I'll pay my respects heading back down.

135
00:12:31.253 --> 00:12:33.880
Walk said that. uh.

136
00:12:34.422 --> 00:12:36.550
you found somebody
to help with the George stuff?

137
00:12:37.342 --> 00:12:38.760
Yeah. we buried him today.

138
00:12:39.594 --> 00:12:40.720
- Marnes?
- Mmm.

139
00:12:41.721 --> 00:12:42.621
Shit.

140
00:12:44.599 --> 00:12:47.477
Hey. Are. um...
Those supposed to be for me?

141
00:12:48.436 --> 00:12:50.188
- Oh. yeah.
- Yeah?

142
00:12:54.609 --> 00:12:58.529
Look. you can't send a guy up 144 levels
with a tin of hush puppies

143
00:12:58.530 --> 00:13:00.781
- and not expect him to eat a couple.
- There's one left.

144
00:13:00.782 --> 00:13:02.200
- I'm a big guy.
- Mmm.

145
00:13:08.248 --> 00:13:11.626
- How are you?
- Good. Yeah. I'm okay.

146
00:13:15.964 --> 00:13:17.173
Walk sent you. didn't she?

147
00:13:19.342 --> 00:13:21.720
Yeah. and Shirley.

148
00:13:22.637 --> 00:13:24.723
Yeah. 'Cause they're worried about me?

149
00:13:25.223 --> 00:13:27.976
Jules.
everybody's worried about everything.

150
00:13:29.394 --> 00:13:32.062
On the way up.
I said hey to my cousin on 72.

151
00:13:32.063 --> 00:13:36.358
and he asked if. um.
it's safe for his kids to go to school.

152
00:13:36.359 --> 00:13:40.154
- It's a dangerous time in the Silo and...
- And you're wondering if I can do this.

153
00:13:40.155 --> 00:13:41.656
No. that's not what I'm saying.

154
00:13:44.200 --> 00:13:46.481
- It's what it sounds like.
- Hey. would you listen to me?

155
00:13:48.038 --> 00:13:50.457
I know you can do anything
you put your mind to.

156
00:13:51.041 --> 00:13:53.710
But I also know
that none of us can do any of this alone.

157
00:13:54.461 --> 00:13:58.672
Now. look. I've never won
Deputy of the Year or nothing.

158
00:13:58.673 --> 00:14:01.801
but if you need anything.

159
00:14:03.303 --> 00:14:04.930
I'm just a tin of hush puppies away.

160
00:14:11.061 --> 00:14:11.961
Deputy.

161
00:14:13.772 --> 00:14:14.773
Sheriff.

162
00:14:17.901 --> 00:14:19.694
- Hey. Hank.
- Yeah?

163
00:16:19.314 --> 00:16:20.315
I don't like you.

164
00:16:21.316 --> 00:16:24.026
- I got that.
- You're not qualified to be sheriff.

165
00:16:24.027 --> 00:16:25.945
Can't disagree. Anything else?

166
00:16:25.946 --> 00:16:28.781
Holston Becker was
the best sheriff this Silo's ever seen.

167
00:16:28.782 --> 00:16:31.450
Marnes told me that something happened
between you two.

168
00:16:31.451 --> 00:16:33.702
and that's why Holston went out to clean.

169
00:16:33.703 --> 00:16:36.706
Hmm. Well. Marnes was wrong.

170
00:16:38.541 --> 00:16:41.294
You took this job to find out
who killed George Wilkins.

171
00:16:42.295 --> 00:16:45.422
When Wilkins died.
the Down Deep deputy sent a message.

172
00:16:45.423 --> 00:16:49.094
Said an engineer named Nichols
claimed Wilkins was murdered.

173
00:16:49.803 --> 00:16:53.306
Now the first thing you do when you
get up here is ask for Wilkins' file.

174
00:16:55.850 --> 00:17:00.146
Here's the deal.
Everything in this office goes through me.

175
00:17:00.897 --> 00:17:02.398
Yeah. you wanna get anything done.

176
00:17:02.399 --> 00:17:05.901
whether it's find out who killed Wilkins
or get a new pencil.

177
00:17:06.777 --> 00:17:08.154
you're gonna do what I want.

178
00:17:09.072 --> 00:17:10.323
What's that?

179
00:17:10.907 --> 00:17:12.242
Find out who killed Marnes.

180
00:17:13.493 --> 00:17:14.868
Right. That's my job. so...

181
00:17:14.869 --> 00:17:17.746
I don't mean just going along
with whatever patsy Judicial serves up.

182
00:17:17.747 --> 00:17:21.083
- I mean. find out who really did it.
- Why would Judicial serve up a patsy?

183
00:17:22.252 --> 00:17:24.920
Because Judge Meadows
doesn't give a shit about the truth.

184
00:17:26.464 --> 00:17:28.717
No. the only thing she cares about
is maintaining order.

185
00:17:29.301 --> 00:17:31.678
And when a mayor
and a deputy get murdered.

186
00:17:32.971 --> 00:17:35.557
things could get disorderly fast.

187
00:17:36.391 --> 00:17:38.934
No. they're gonna wanna find
the nearest warm body to pin it on.

188
00:17:38.935 --> 00:17:40.227
Expect you to go along with it.

189
00:17:40.228 --> 00:17:42.521
so you can keep the shiny badge
and the nice apartment.

190
00:17:42.522 --> 00:17:44.982
But that would be a mistake on your part.

191
00:17:44.983 --> 00:17:47.736
because they also wanna get you out
and Billings in.

192
00:17:48.612 --> 00:17:49.779
Isn't that what you want?

193
00:17:52.073 --> 00:17:55.826
Honestly. I may want you
to find out who killed Marnes.

194
00:17:55.827 --> 00:17:58.413
but Marnes. he wouldn't give a shit.

195
00:17:59.372 --> 00:18:01.874
He just wouldn't want
Judicial sending some poor bastard

196
00:18:01.875 --> 00:18:03.793
out to clean that doesn't deserve it.

197
00:18:18.350 --> 00:18:19.683
I'll be back after lunch.

198
00:18:19.684 --> 00:18:21.394
Where are you going?

199
00:18:22.771 --> 00:18:24.813
I'm gonna try and figure out
who killed Marnes.

200
00:18:24.814 --> 00:18:27.067
Well. you should take
Deputy Billings with you.

201
00:18:27.651 --> 00:18:30.069
He knows the Pact. and you don't.

202
00:18:30.070 --> 00:18:32.071
If you get this wrong.
even if you get who did it.

203
00:18:32.072 --> 00:18:33.782
Judicial will throw it out.

204
00:18:37.118 --> 00:18:38.119
Let's go.

205
00:19:01.268 --> 00:19:02.561
Hey.

206
00:19:03.061 --> 00:19:04.354
You Charles Martin?

207
00:19:04.938 --> 00:19:05.772
What if I am?

208
00:19:05.773 --> 00:19:07.982
You rob a string of apartments
15 years ago?

209
00:19:07.983 --> 00:19:09.567
I did my time.

210
00:19:09.568 --> 00:19:11.235
We just wanna know
where you were last night.

211
00:19:11.236 --> 00:19:13.946
- You asking if I killed Marnes?
- Didn't say anything about...

212
00:19:13.947 --> 00:19:15.740
Don't tell me he died naturally.

213
00:19:16.575 --> 00:19:19.536
If Marnes just had a heart attack.
then life really sucks.

214
00:19:21.538 --> 00:19:22.956
But it wasn't me.

215
00:19:23.456 --> 00:19:26.710
I've been down on 62. getting tests.

216
00:19:27.419 --> 00:19:28.587
Okay.

217
00:19:29.296 --> 00:19:30.297
Thank you.

218
00:19:32.090 --> 00:19:33.841
Even if he wasn't in the hospital.

219
00:19:33.842 --> 00:19:35.676
I'm sure he wouldn't have
been a match for Marnes.

220
00:19:35.677 --> 00:19:37.762
You saw his hand? He's got the Syndrome.

221
00:19:39.097 --> 00:19:40.098
Where next?

222
00:19:44.102 --> 00:19:45.687
- What?
- Where... Where do you live?

223
00:19:46.229 --> 00:19:49.273
- A couple levels down.
- Okay. Why don't you go home for lunch?

224
00:19:49.274 --> 00:19:51.984
I'm sure your wife and your daughter
would love to see you.

225
00:19:51.985 --> 00:19:53.069
It's only 11:00.

226
00:19:53.904 --> 00:19:55.280
I know. It's just...

227
00:19:55.906 --> 00:19:59.200
it's been a lot. and. um. I need a moment.

228
00:19:59.826 --> 00:20:03.330
I'm gonna grab a sandwich. read the Pact.
I hear great things about it.

229
00:20:04.706 --> 00:20:06.333
I'll be back in the office by 1:00.

230
00:20:17.135 --> 00:20:19.845
I stopped by and saw him
and his bloody nose.

231
00:20:19.846 --> 00:20:21.555
Who gave him a bloody nose?

232
00:20:21.556 --> 00:20:23.307
One of his many fans.

233
00:20:23.308 --> 00:20:26.519
Patrick. we all knew she was headed
for the farm the minute she met you.

234
00:20:48.875 --> 00:20:51.044
Patrick Kennedy. it's the sheriff.
Can you open up?

235
00:22:48.703 --> 00:22:49.913
Who are you looking for?

236
00:22:52.582 --> 00:22:53.667
Patrick Kennedy.

237
00:22:54.251 --> 00:22:55.252
He's not here.

238
00:23:05.303 --> 00:23:06.596
"...serious violations.

239
00:23:07.180 --> 00:23:09.223
both of which
will be initially investigated

240
00:23:09.224 --> 00:23:13.936
by the Department of the Sheriff. being
reported to Judicial within one hour."

241
00:23:13.937 --> 00:23:15.772
Read the part about accountability.

242
00:23:17.566 --> 00:23:19.276
- Yes?
- It's Paul Billings.

243
00:23:21.778 --> 00:23:23.154
Come in. Paul.

244
00:23:27.075 --> 00:23:28.535
Paul. you know Doug Trumbull.

245
00:23:29.911 --> 00:23:33.039
- Of course.
- Doug's a candidate to be my shadow.

246
00:23:36.251 --> 00:23:37.961
We'll get to the rest of this later.

247
00:23:49.222 --> 00:23:51.682
Doug Trumbull? Your shadow?

248
00:23:51.683 --> 00:23:53.976
I only said he's a candidate.

249
00:23:53.977 --> 00:23:57.147
He asked if he could be considered.
I didn't have the heart to say no.

250
00:23:57.647 --> 00:24:00.317
Besides. it's always good
to have an excuse to read the Pact.

251
00:24:02.402 --> 00:24:06.238
Our new sheriff okay with you coming back
to Judicial your first day on the job?

252
00:24:06.239 --> 00:24:07.657
She thinks I went home for lunch.

253
00:24:09.367 --> 00:24:10.535
What can I do for you?

254
00:24:34.100 --> 00:24:36.227
- Hey. Kennedy.
- Hey. what are you doing here?

255
00:24:36.228 --> 00:24:38.520
Maintenance said
this is where I'd find you.

256
00:24:38.521 --> 00:24:40.398
Mmm.
I was sad to hear about Deputy Marnes.

257
00:24:41.816 --> 00:24:44.236
I'm kidding. I was fucking giddy.

258
00:24:45.320 --> 00:24:48.948
Yesterday you said there were two reasons
why we were stupid

259
00:24:48.949 --> 00:24:50.741
for wanting to talk to your wife.

260
00:24:50.742 --> 00:24:53.662
First was. she's dead.
Uh. what's the second one?

261
00:24:55.664 --> 00:24:57.873
You know what. I'm a little confused.
Are you arresting me?

262
00:24:57.874 --> 00:24:59.708
- Nope.
- Then what are you doing?

263
00:24:59.709 --> 00:25:01.169
I'm putting you somewhere safe.

264
00:25:06.591 --> 00:25:07.801
- Hey. Sandy.
- Hi.

265
00:25:14.099 --> 00:25:16.476
- How's it going?
- Slowly.

266
00:25:17.936 --> 00:25:20.312
As much as I revere that thing.
if I can't sleep.

267
00:25:20.313 --> 00:25:22.274
- I read a couple pages and I'm out.
- Mmm.

268
00:25:23.775 --> 00:25:26.236
- How was lunch?
- Can I sit?

269
00:25:30.115 --> 00:25:33.201
I didn't go home. I went to Judicial.

270
00:25:33.785 --> 00:25:35.536
Oh. wow. Reporting to Sims already?

271
00:25:35.537 --> 00:25:37.288
I didn't know
I'd fucked up that badly yet.

272
00:25:37.289 --> 00:25:39.123
I know it's gonna take a lot
to earn your trust.

273
00:25:39.124 --> 00:25:41.959
and this might not be the best first step.

274
00:25:41.960 --> 00:25:44.503
But I wanted to see
how their investigation was going.

275
00:25:44.504 --> 00:25:46.171
Judicial has its own investigation?

276
00:25:46.172 --> 00:25:48.174
They get level rep reports first.

277
00:25:48.842 --> 00:25:52.761
And they get reports from people
who don't officially exist.

278
00:25:52.762 --> 00:25:53.930
Right. listeners.

279
00:25:54.681 --> 00:25:56.266
Not what we call them. but yeah.

280
00:25:57.017 --> 00:25:59.102
- What do you call them?
- Friends of the Silo.

281
00:25:59.686 --> 00:26:00.686
Hmm.

282
00:26:00.687 --> 00:26:03.064
None of what they say
is admissible in court.

283
00:26:04.608 --> 00:26:05.609
But...

284
00:26:06.401 --> 00:26:07.902
They can provide suggestions.

285
00:26:07.903 --> 00:26:11.907
- Wow. you look in pain just saying that.
- It's not in the Pact. so I don't like it.

286
00:26:12.741 --> 00:26:15.201
Hmm. Who are the friends suggesting?

287
00:26:16.202 --> 00:26:17.661
Ralf Melby.

288
00:26:17.662 --> 00:26:20.205
He works down in Paper. first shift.

289
00:26:20.206 --> 00:26:22.875
He could've made it to the Mids
to poison their water.

290
00:26:22.876 --> 00:26:25.294
he could've made it up last night
to get Marnes.

291
00:26:25.295 --> 00:26:29.298
"Gambler. thief. two minor assaults."
Why... Why now?

292
00:26:29.299 --> 00:26:30.759
Have to ask him.

293
00:26:35.055 --> 00:26:37.473
Hey. Sandy.
can you get me an arrest warrant?

294
00:26:37.474 --> 00:26:39.058
- For who?
- Patrick Kennedy.

295
00:26:39.059 --> 00:26:41.894
- What? No. Ralf Melby.
- Kennedy first.

296
00:26:41.895 --> 00:26:44.188
And then can you call me
on the radio once you have it?

297
00:26:44.189 --> 00:26:47.651
- Where are you going?
- You got messages. Um. Hey.

298
00:26:49.486 --> 00:26:50.487
Hey.

299
00:26:51.071 --> 00:26:53.281
Nichols. can you just stop?

300
00:26:54.532 --> 00:26:56.533
- Hey.
- I don't have time for messages...

301
00:26:56.534 --> 00:27:00.747
I don't have any fucking messages.
I just... I need to know what's going on.

302
00:27:02.624 --> 00:27:06.877
Billings went to his friends in Judicial
and came back with a name. Ralf Melby.

303
00:27:06.878 --> 00:27:09.129
They want me to waste my time
arresting Melby

304
00:27:09.130 --> 00:27:10.422
while they get their patsy.

305
00:27:10.423 --> 00:27:11.507
- Patrick Kennedy.
- Yeah.

306
00:27:11.508 --> 00:27:12.967
That's gonna make me look incompetent.

307
00:27:12.968 --> 00:27:15.804
they'll send me back to Mechanical.
and Billings gets the badge.

308
00:27:16.304 --> 00:27:18.264
You sure they're setting up Kennedy?

309
00:27:18.265 --> 00:27:20.724
I know a search is gonna turn up
rat poison

310
00:27:20.725 --> 00:27:22.184
and a drawing from Marnes's wall.

311
00:27:22.185 --> 00:27:23.228
How do you know that?

312
00:27:24.938 --> 00:27:27.690
If he's their patsy.
you requesting an arrest warrant

313
00:27:27.691 --> 00:27:30.067
means Judicial's gonna send a goon
to get him right away.

314
00:27:30.068 --> 00:27:31.152
That's why I'm going.

315
00:27:32.904 --> 00:27:39.077
Seven. six. five. four. three. two. one.

316
00:27:42.080 --> 00:27:44.124
All the best to competitors.

317
00:27:53.967 --> 00:27:56.344
Judicial. Open up.

318
00:27:57.345 --> 00:27:58.597
Looking for Patrick Kennedy?

319
00:27:59.931 --> 00:28:02.725
Yeah. it took a while for Housing
to find out his wife died last year.

320
00:28:02.726 --> 00:28:04.727
They moved him to a single. like.
six months ago

321
00:28:04.728 --> 00:28:06.604
and moved an older couple in here.

322
00:28:06.605 --> 00:28:09.690
Maybe that's why Judicial's database
still has this down as his place.

323
00:28:09.691 --> 00:28:10.775
I don't know.

324
00:28:11.276 --> 00:28:13.653
I only know this 'cause Marnes and I
came here yesterday.

325
00:28:14.696 --> 00:28:16.256
I guess everyone makes mistakes. right?

326
00:28:17.365 --> 00:28:19.618
Yours was planting evidence
in the wrong apartment.

327
00:28:26.082 --> 00:28:27.000
Hey!

328
00:28:34.883 --> 00:28:35.884
Watch it!

329
00:28:47.062 --> 00:28:48.521
Go! Get out...

330
00:29:33.900 --> 00:29:36.820
- What are you doing? Asshole.
- Hey! What the fuck?

331
00:30:20.864 --> 00:30:21.990
Mommy. look.

332
00:30:37.714 --> 00:30:39.673
- There's someone up there.
- Watch out!

333
00:30:39.674 --> 00:30:40.926
Somebody help her!

334
00:30:46.765 --> 00:30:48.642
- Somebody help her!
- Hey. somebody help her!

335
00:31:06.159 --> 00:31:07.160
Go.

336
00:31:19.714 --> 00:31:21.757
<i>I think I know who it was
you were chasing.</i>

337
00:31:21.758 --> 00:31:25.053
Doug Trumbull. Judicial Security.
I'll get an arrest warrant.

338
00:31:25.845 --> 00:31:27.972
I wish you waited for me to come with you.

339
00:31:27.973 --> 00:31:30.516
Well. I was just gonna
check out Kennedy's apartment.

340
00:31:30.517 --> 00:31:33.037
I didn't think someone was gonna try
and throw me over the rail.

341
00:31:37.023 --> 00:31:39.024
Hey. what apartment number
did you have for Kennedy?

342
00:31:39.025 --> 00:31:40.819
2215. why?

343
00:31:41.736 --> 00:31:44.155
I think maybe Kennedy didn't have
anything to do with this.

344
00:32:19.482 --> 00:32:22.193
Douglas. What are you doing here?

345
00:32:23.904 --> 00:32:26.990
- I followed you once.
- Ah. that shows initiative.

346
00:32:27.741 --> 00:32:28.992
Skill.

347
00:32:29.659 --> 00:32:32.120
And a very troubling insubordination.

348
00:32:33.747 --> 00:32:34.705
I'm sorry.

349
00:32:34.706 --> 00:32:37.500
Do you have any idea
what's behind this door?

350
00:32:38.084 --> 00:32:39.794
- No. sir.
- Good.

351
00:32:40.378 --> 00:32:43.088
If I choose you to shadow me.
you will know.

352
00:32:43.089 --> 00:32:44.549
What happened to your hand?

353
00:32:49.054 --> 00:32:51.097
- You have the note?
- Yeah.

354
00:32:58.772 --> 00:33:01.607
Good. I think there's still a way
to make this work.

355
00:33:01.608 --> 00:33:03.526
- How?
- Let me figure that out.

356
00:33:05.862 --> 00:33:07.948
This is my favorite time.

357
00:33:09.991 --> 00:33:12.369
So quiet. so still.

358
00:33:14.079 --> 00:33:16.831
Now. Douglas. that door I came out of.

359
00:33:18.375 --> 00:33:22.087
first time I saw it.
my father showed it to me.

360
00:33:24.464 --> 00:33:25.715
He was a janitor.

361
00:33:26.716 --> 00:33:30.136
People looked down on him. On our family.

362
00:33:30.804 --> 00:33:33.223
We all know the philosophy of the Pact.

363
00:33:33.765 --> 00:33:36.851
Everyone contributes
to the survival of the Silo.

364
00:33:38.144 --> 00:33:40.188
But a janitor's still a janitor.

365
00:33:43.567 --> 00:33:45.777
And I was just a janitor's boy.

366
00:33:47.153 --> 00:33:49.405
My mother treated my father
like he was nothing.

367
00:33:49.406 --> 00:33:51.366
and he said nothing in return.

368
00:33:53.285 --> 00:33:58.623
When I was 14. I got into a conflict
with one of my classmates.

369
00:33:59.291 --> 00:34:02.168
Richard Elliot. Ah. he tormented me.

370
00:34:02.669 --> 00:34:03.878
My father found out.

371
00:34:03.879 --> 00:34:07.757
and I was terrified he was gonna try to do
something about it and only make it worse.

372
00:34:08.675 --> 00:34:09.675
But he didn't.

373
00:34:12.512 --> 00:34:14.306
Part of me was disappointed.

374
00:34:15.765 --> 00:34:17.767
Then one day. I get to school

375
00:34:19.311 --> 00:34:20.811
and Richard Elliot's crying.

376
00:34:21.313 --> 00:34:25.566
Seems his father's been reassigned
to a job on 125. and they have to move.

377
00:34:25.567 --> 00:34:28.945
Just like that. my problem went away.

378
00:34:31.448 --> 00:34:32.657
I was wondering if...

379
00:34:35.201 --> 00:34:38.079
if maybe my dad
had something to do with it.

380
00:34:40.332 --> 00:34:43.876
But he was just a janitor. Right?

381
00:34:45.586 --> 00:34:49.382
Then. one morning. he says to me.

382
00:34:51.175 --> 00:34:53.010
"Any more problems with that bully?"

383
00:34:54.054 --> 00:34:56.471
I just looked at him.
It was something in the way he said it.

384
00:34:56.472 --> 00:34:58.475
I just looked at him and asked. "How?"

385
00:35:00.727 --> 00:35:04.981
He said he wanted to show me something.
He took me to that door.

386
00:35:05.565 --> 00:35:07.650
He said if I wanted to shadow him.

387
00:35:07.651 --> 00:35:11.905
I would have to make a decision
that would change my life forever.

388
00:35:13.698 --> 00:35:15.407
If I went through that door.

389
00:35:15.408 --> 00:35:18.245
I could never tell anyone
what was on the other side.

390
00:35:18.870 --> 00:35:22.040
Not my friends. not my family.
not my wife.

391
00:35:22.624 --> 00:35:27.169
They might think that I was nothing
more than a bookkeeper. or a clerk.

392
00:35:27.170 --> 00:35:28.296
or a janitor.

393
00:35:30.006 --> 00:35:31.299
But I would know the truth.

394
00:35:32.050 --> 00:35:33.843
That the people behind that door

395
00:35:35.178 --> 00:35:38.265
do the most important work of the Silo.

396
00:35:40.767 --> 00:35:43.770
Work that keeps 10.000 people alive.

397
00:35:47.732 --> 00:35:49.109
You fucked up. Doug.

398
00:35:50.235 --> 00:35:53.405
Twice. Very badly.

399
00:35:54.614 --> 00:35:57.449
- You fucked up with George Wilkins...
- You know what happened?

400
00:35:57.450 --> 00:35:59.703
...and you fucked up with Patrick Kennedy.

401
00:36:03.248 --> 00:36:06.835
But I've fucked up worse. Many times.

402
00:36:08.169 --> 00:36:11.381
We're human beings doing the best we can.

403
00:36:12.465 --> 00:36:17.012
What I'm looking for in a shadow
is drive and dedication.

404
00:36:19.598 --> 00:36:20.932
I've made my decision.

405
00:36:25.353 --> 00:36:31.026
Douglas Trumbull. do you. of clear mind
and conscience. pledge to be my shadow?

406
00:36:31.651 --> 00:36:32.551
Yes.

407
00:36:33.695 --> 00:36:39.284
Are you willing to do anything to serve
and protect the people of the Silo?

408
00:36:39.910 --> 00:36:40.993
Yes.

409
00:36:40.994 --> 00:36:44.414
Are you willing
to give everything you have

410
00:36:45.624 --> 00:36:48.751
to serve and protect
the people of the Silo?

411
00:36:48.752 --> 00:36:49.835
Yes.

412
00:36:49.836 --> 00:36:50.921
Good.

413
00:36:53.590 --> 00:36:55.383
No!

414
00:37:03.642 --> 00:37:06.644
Douglas Trumbull
killed Mayor Jahns and Deputy Marnes.

415
00:37:06.645 --> 00:37:08.896
and he wanted to frame Patrick Kennedy
for the murders.

416
00:37:08.897 --> 00:37:12.149
His intent wasn't only to. uh.
frame Kennedy.

417
00:37:12.150 --> 00:37:14.610
but to kill him
and make it look like suicide.

418
00:37:14.611 --> 00:37:16.779
So when I confronted Trumbull

419
00:37:16.780 --> 00:37:21.451
about planting evidence in an apartment
no longer occupied by Kennedy. he ran.

420
00:37:22.202 --> 00:37:24.496
Last night.
knowing his arrest was inevitable.

421
00:37:25.330 --> 00:37:26.705
Trumbull took his own life.

422
00:37:26.706 --> 00:37:30.460
There's a... There's a note in there
that we. uh. found in his pocket.

423
00:37:31.169 --> 00:37:36.132
We think he was gonna plant it on Kennedy.
Strangely. it kinda works for him too.

424
00:37:37.634 --> 00:37:38.884
We. um. we don't know...

425
00:37:38.885 --> 00:37:40.302
Why.

426
00:37:40.303 --> 00:37:44.139
You don't know why
a seven-year employee of Judicial

427
00:37:44.140 --> 00:37:46.058
would want to murder the mayor and Marnes.

428
00:37:46.059 --> 00:37:48.269
Well. no. but we...

429
00:37:48.270 --> 00:37:50.670
I didn't work closely with Trumbull.
but I saw no sign of it.

430
00:37:51.231 --> 00:37:53.858
Mr. Sims. did you see any indication?

431
00:37:54.568 --> 00:37:58.070
I mean. Marnes was deputy in the Mids back
in the day when Trumbull was growing up.

432
00:37:58.071 --> 00:38:01.865
Maybe... Maybe they had some
rough encounters back then.

433
00:38:01.866 --> 00:38:03.660
I don't know. We're gonna look into it.

434
00:38:07.205 --> 00:38:08.790
Don't spend any more time on him.

435
00:38:09.541 --> 00:38:12.627
We have the killer of Mayor Jahns
and Deputy Marnes. and...

436
00:38:14.713 --> 00:38:15.714
...he's dead.

437
00:38:18.675 --> 00:38:21.176
This should quell the rumors
and conspiracy theories.

438
00:38:21.177 --> 00:38:22.387
Indeed.

439
00:38:26.516 --> 00:38:28.143
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

440
00:38:29.477 --> 00:38:32.646
I'll take the rat poison to the farms.
you take the rest to the office?

441
00:38:32.647 --> 00:38:33.732
Yep.

442
00:38:36.860 --> 00:38:39.361
You already knew that the drawing
and the rat poison

443
00:38:39.362 --> 00:38:41.071
were in the apartment before we looked.

444
00:38:41.072 --> 00:38:43.241
- Mm-hmm.
- When did you go in?

445
00:38:43.825 --> 00:38:46.076
When you were talking
to your Judicial friends.

446
00:38:46.077 --> 00:38:49.455
- How'd you get in?
- I learned some things in Mechanical.

447
00:38:49.456 --> 00:38:51.206
You clearly
didn't read the section of the Pact

448
00:38:51.207 --> 00:38:54.126
- about illegal search and seizure.
- No. I did.

449
00:38:54.127 --> 00:38:55.807
Why didn't you tell me
what you were doing?

450
00:38:56.296 --> 00:38:58.632
- 'Cause I didn't trust you.
- Do you now?

451
00:38:59.216 --> 00:39:02.177
Yeah. Sure. As much as you trust me.

452
00:39:16.024 --> 00:39:20.153
So you don't worry what happened
to me tomorrow. I've been reassigned.

453
00:39:21.571 --> 00:39:23.990
- What?
- To the station on 105.

454
00:39:25.659 --> 00:39:26.743
Why?

455
00:39:27.702 --> 00:39:28.870
I requested it.

456
00:39:30.538 --> 00:39:31.706
'Cause of me?

457
00:39:32.666 --> 00:39:34.334
No. I've got family down there.

458
00:39:37.963 --> 00:39:41.131
Wait. so when...
When you said if I wanted your help.

459
00:39:41.132 --> 00:39:43.134
I had to find out who killed Marnes.

460
00:39:44.010 --> 00:39:49.307
Yeah. I'm sorry. I didn't think
you'd be able to do that. really.

461
00:39:51.518 --> 00:39:53.102
Any chance you'd change your mind?

462
00:39:53.103 --> 00:39:56.523
No. I've had enough of the Up Top.

463
00:39:58.441 --> 00:40:00.193
You know.
there are a few things I'll miss.

464
00:40:01.778 --> 00:40:03.618
but I won't miss the feeling
I'm being watched.

465
00:40:05.365 --> 00:40:06.265
By who?

466
00:40:07.909 --> 00:40:09.244
I don't know by who.

467
00:40:10.537 --> 00:40:11.621
Or how.

468
00:40:13.164 --> 00:40:19.254
Hey. You know. when I got here. you said
you didn't know what Down Deepers ate.

469
00:40:19.921 --> 00:40:21.046
You got family on 105?

470
00:40:21.047 --> 00:40:22.715
That's lower Mids. not Down Deep.

471
00:40:22.716 --> 00:40:24.008
- Right.
- Our kind don't eat babies.

472
00:40:24.009 --> 00:40:25.343
Mm-hmm.

473
00:40:28.430 --> 00:40:29.514
You did a good thing.

474
00:40:32.142 --> 00:40:36.854
I mean. Patrick Kennedy's an awful
human being but he didn't deserve to die.

475
00:40:36.855 --> 00:40:39.648
- Not for something he didn't do.
- I'm just happy that I didn't...

476
00:40:39.649 --> 00:40:41.985
Don't make a big deal out of it.
I still don't like you.

477
00:40:44.070 --> 00:40:45.071
Sheriff.

478
00:40:55.999 --> 00:40:57.499
<i>Can I pour you a drink?</i>

479
00:40:57.500 --> 00:41:00.544
I'm going through Mayor Jahns's collection
pretty fast.

480
00:41:00.545 --> 00:41:02.338
- No. I'm good. Thanks.
- You sure?

481
00:41:02.339 --> 00:41:04.299
- Yeah.
- Have a seat.

482
00:41:08.762 --> 00:41:14.141
Now. as much as I hate to give Sims
the satisfaction.

483
00:41:14.142 --> 00:41:16.393
I think he may have been right.

484
00:41:16.394 --> 00:41:18.646
The Race to the Top was a good tonic.

485
00:41:18.647 --> 00:41:21.316
but what we really need
is a Forgiveness Holiday.

486
00:41:22.525 --> 00:41:25.694
People go a little wild when we have one.

487
00:41:25.695 --> 00:41:28.156
so I'm gonna need you
and your deputies everywhere.

488
00:41:29.908 --> 00:41:30.909
Okay.

489
00:41:31.993 --> 00:41:33.995
That's not the only thing
I wanted to discuss.

490
00:41:35.038 --> 00:41:39.626
I wanted to say that I was wrong
about you.

491
00:41:40.627 --> 00:41:46.131
I didn't see why Holston would want you
to be sheriff. but now I think I do.

492
00:41:46.132 --> 00:41:48.301
So. for as long as I'm mayor.

493
00:41:48.885 --> 00:41:52.889
which I sincerely hope won't be
for more than a few months.

494
00:41:54.015 --> 00:41:56.393
I wanna help you in any way I can.

495
00:41:56.977 --> 00:41:58.436
Is there anything you need now?

496
00:42:01.356 --> 00:42:05.442
- Two days off.
- You've been sheriff for a minute?

497
00:42:05.443 --> 00:42:07.361
I need to get back down to Mechanical.

498
00:42:07.362 --> 00:42:10.030
I didn't think I'd last
so. I didn't pack much. so...

499
00:42:10.031 --> 00:42:11.949
We have porters that can do that.

500
00:42:11.950 --> 00:42:15.452
I'd like to say goodbyes
and stuff. you know?

501
00:42:15.453 --> 00:42:18.832
All right. We'll see you in a couple days.

502
00:42:20.333 --> 00:42:21.334
Thanks.

503
00:42:40.979 --> 00:42:42.230
Hey.

504
00:42:42.981 --> 00:42:44.065
Hey.

505
00:42:44.900 --> 00:42:46.234
What are you working on?

506
00:42:48.111 --> 00:42:49.321
You wanna come see?

507
00:42:58.455 --> 00:43:02.918
So. when it's clear at night.
there are these lights in the sky.

508
00:43:05.879 --> 00:43:08.214
Hmm. What are they?

509
00:43:08.215 --> 00:43:09.507
I have no idea.

510
00:43:10.759 --> 00:43:14.136
But I've been watching them long enough
to see these patterns.

511
00:43:14.137 --> 00:43:19.309
They repeat. like they're. uh.
like they're traveling in this big circle.

512
00:43:22.646 --> 00:43:23.855
Here.

513
00:43:25.857 --> 00:43:26.858
Here.

514
00:43:30.237 --> 00:43:31.238
You see it?

515
00:43:34.407 --> 00:43:35.784
I see a "W".

516
00:43:37.202 --> 00:43:39.621
- Never noticed that before.
- Yeah. well. now you have.

517
00:43:44.167 --> 00:43:48.046
I'll just add it to the list of
things we don't know anything about.

518
00:44:41.850 --> 00:44:44.435
<i>Did you know there are lights
in the sky at night?</i>

519
00:44:44.436 --> 00:44:45.519
<i>How do you mean?</i>

520
00:44:45.520 --> 00:44:49.064
Well. the display in the Up Top cafeteria
is better than ours.

521
00:44:49.065 --> 00:44:52.485
- What a surprise.
- There are lights in the night sky.

522
00:44:52.986 --> 00:44:54.070
Yeah. what are they?

523
00:44:54.779 --> 00:44:56.698
I thought maybe you'd know.

524
00:44:57.282 --> 00:44:59.909
You know. Hank ate all
but one of the hush puppies you sent.

525
00:44:59.910 --> 00:45:03.163
Hmm? I kinda thought he'd eat 'em all.

526
00:45:03.788 --> 00:45:04.915
He's a big guy.

527
00:45:06.625 --> 00:45:07.959
How old is this?

528
00:45:08.627 --> 00:45:09.628
What day is it?

529
00:45:13.089 --> 00:45:16.927
So. how's it going in that fancy new job
of yours up there?

530
00:45:18.261 --> 00:45:19.595
- Fine.
- Fine? Really?

531
00:45:19.596 --> 00:45:21.305
- Mm-hmm.
- You know. Tommy Marshall

532
00:45:21.306 --> 00:45:24.142
was working on a ventilation fan
at the foot of the stairs.

533
00:45:24.684 --> 00:45:28.396
This missed his head by an inch.

534
00:45:28.980 --> 00:45:30.940
People saw you hanging from the rails.

535
00:45:30.941 --> 00:45:35.070
Jules. you don't think that kind of story
gets around? What the fuck is going on?

536
00:45:35.654 --> 00:45:37.029
- I can't tell you.
- You can't tell me...

537
00:45:37.030 --> 00:45:38.156
No. I can't.

538
00:45:40.700 --> 00:45:43.911
Goddamn it.
This isn't supposed to be the deal.

539
00:45:43.912 --> 00:45:46.830
We're supposed to go about our business.
keeping the Silo humming.

540
00:45:46.831 --> 00:45:49.625
and they're not supposed to do things
like murder people.

541
00:45:49.626 --> 00:45:52.336
Bodies start falling.
people start asking questions.

542
00:45:52.337 --> 00:45:55.673
Pretty soon. asking questions turns
into demanding answers.

543
00:45:55.674 --> 00:45:58.467
- and if folks don't like the answers...
- Hey. hey. hey.

544
00:45:58.468 --> 00:46:01.304
You're talking about rebellion?
I'm right here. I'm sheriff.

545
00:46:01.930 --> 00:46:02.830
Ridiculous.

546
00:46:04.474 --> 00:46:07.017
Anyway. did you find
that hard drive you were looking for?

547
00:46:07.018 --> 00:46:09.311
No. not yet. Holston hid a file on George.

548
00:46:09.312 --> 00:46:11.565
but there was nothing in it
that I didn't already know.

549
00:46:12.732 --> 00:46:14.441
Did you make headway
with the thing I left you?

550
00:46:14.442 --> 00:46:15.527
Yes. I did.

551
00:46:16.152 --> 00:46:19.655
So. I recognized the type of lens

552
00:46:19.656 --> 00:46:23.158
from those cameras they use
to make pictures for ID's.

553
00:46:23.159 --> 00:46:27.664
But those are very simple.
This... This is not simple.

554
00:46:29.332 --> 00:46:30.333
Take a look.

555
00:46:36.756 --> 00:46:37.799
This help you?

556
00:46:40.093 --> 00:46:41.969
No. You got anything more powerful?

557
00:46:41.970 --> 00:46:45.097
Like the thing your mother made?
Lining up two lenses?

558
00:46:45.098 --> 00:46:46.682
Yeah. like we used on the rabbit.

559
00:46:46.683 --> 00:46:50.394
Yeah. and Judicial destroyed it.
Do you know why Judicial destroyed it?

560
00:46:50.395 --> 00:46:53.064
- No.
- Have you read the Pact?

561
00:46:53.648 --> 00:46:55.608
No. and you're. like.
the tenth person to ask me that.

562
00:46:55.609 --> 00:46:58.277
Well. this is the real reason
why I wanted you to come down.

563
00:46:58.278 --> 00:47:01.781
For me. there are two big mysteries
about the Pact.

564
00:47:02.365 --> 00:47:03.532
One.

565
00:47:03.533 --> 00:47:07.369
They stipulate that we can't mechanize
the way we go up and down in the Silo.

566
00:47:07.370 --> 00:47:09.414
- Mm-hmm. Yeah.
- No lifts. no pulleys.

567
00:47:09.915 --> 00:47:14.169
Two.
No magnification beyond a certain power.

568
00:47:15.295 --> 00:47:18.381
So. a relic like this is gonna get you
more than a slap on the wrist.

569
00:47:18.882 --> 00:47:20.884
Something with wiring this small.

570
00:47:21.468 --> 00:47:23.386
the effect is gonna be
a lot more dramatic.

571
00:47:26.389 --> 00:47:30.226
And from what you're not telling me.
seems to me there's a long list of people

572
00:47:30.227 --> 00:47:33.771
who've died recently
under questionable circumstances.

573
00:47:33.772 --> 00:47:36.023
What's to stop you being
the next one on the list?

574
00:47:36.024 --> 00:47:36.941
I'll be careful.

575
00:47:36.942 --> 00:47:39.652
Put the badge in an envelope.
give it to a porter.

576
00:47:39.653 --> 00:47:41.779
I need to find out what happened.

577
00:47:41.780 --> 00:47:44.907
Two days ago. Bernard wanted nothing
more than to send me out to clean

578
00:47:44.908 --> 00:47:47.452
for snagging two boxes
of shitty heat tape.

579
00:47:48.453 --> 00:47:53.583
I solve two murders. and he can't wait
to work with me. They trust me. Walk.

580
00:47:54.584 --> 00:47:56.168
I need to open up an investigation

581
00:47:56.169 --> 00:47:58.504
that allows me to look into
what happened to George.

582
00:47:58.505 --> 00:48:01.216
And how are you gonna do that
without tipping them off?

583
00:48:02.217 --> 00:48:03.718
I gotta use the right bait.
